  "subject": [],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "synopsis",
      "abstract": "This Act requires the Court of Chancery, beginning January 1, 2027, to audio record all public proceedings and make such recordings publicly available.  Such recordings must be made available within a reasonable time after the conclusion of the proceeding.  The presiding judicial officer may, for good cause shown, restrict public access to an audio recording in whole or in part."
    }
